OL,3,CRobert Peston: Burnham almost has the
OL,4,Ckeys to Downing Street
OL,6,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FHaving spent the last few days with
OL,12,FStarmer at the G7 in France and having
OL,13,Finterviewed him about this, I am in no
OL,14,Fdoubt his mood is to fight - partly
OL,15,Fbecause, I am told, his erstwhile
OL,16,Fadviser Morgan McSweeney is telling
OL,17,Fhim Burnham will flake in a contest
OL,18,Fand that he will win.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31008
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1781873291
OL,3,CRobert Peston: Burnham almost has the
OL,4,Ckeys to Downing Street
OL,6,FIf Starmer does choose to fight, it
OL,7,Fwill all get very messy for him very
OL,8,Ffast.
OL,10,FBecause he will have to decide whether
OL,11,Fministers can publicly endorse
OL,12,FBurnham, as they will want to do, and
OL,13,Fkeep their jobs.
OL,15,FIf he tells them the price of keeping
OL,16,Ftheir jobs is NOT to nominate Burnham,
OL,17,Fsome - maybe many - will resign, and
OL,18,FStarmer will preside over a re-run of
OL,19,Fthe mass resignations that destroyed
OL,20,FBoris Johnson at the end of his time
OL,21,Fas prime minister.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
